From 2b2c47d2bcbf1c227daa653b4b8b463e39f865fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sam Thursfield <sam.thursfield@codethink.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 12:44:32 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 03/11] FDSDK 26.08: Use new `-maybe` elements

FDSDK 26.08 introduces support for some new architectures where not all
of the components can be built. The workaround for that is to add
`components/*-maybe.bst` elements that, on most platforms, contain the
element but on platforms where it can't be built, contain nothing.
---
